OL,4,C'perpetuates bias and discrimination'
OL,6,F"I am proud that Liverpool Parish
OL,7,FChurch continues to make a public
OL,8,Fdeclaration of the dignity of all
OL,9,Fpeople, in the knowledge that we are
OL,10,Fall made in God's image.
OL,12,F"I must therefore pay tribute to the
OL,13,Fpeople of Liverpool Parish Church and
OL,14,Fto those both locally and nationally
OL,15,Fwho have spoken with courageous and
OL,16,Fprophetic voices.
OL,18,F"I would like to thank the two Bishops
OL,19,Fof Liverpool under whom I have served
OL,20,Ffor their exceptional leadership on
OL,21,Fthese matters.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/10
